The increase in identifiable assets from June 30, 1994 to June 30, 1995 is
primarily the result of the Bull acquisition, which occurred in January
1995. The increase in identifiable assets from June 30, 1993 to June 30, 1994 is
due principally to the implementation of fresh-start reporting, which resulted
in the establishment of intangible assets.

NOTE I--COMMITMENTS AND CONTINGENCIES

LEASES:  Rental expense amounted to $17.6 million for the year ended June 30,
1995, $16.7 million for the nine months ended June 30, 1994, $8.0 million for
the three months ended September 30, 1993, and $29.0 million in fiscal 1993.  As
part of the Chapter 11 proceeding, the Company rejected or renegotiated leases
and, in some circumstances, replaced leases with smaller, shorter-term leases
to conform to the Company's reduced space needs.  Future minimum lease
commitments on noncancelable leases are (in millions):  $33.8 in fiscal 1996,
$30.1 in fiscal 1997, $26.5 in fiscal 1998, $21.9 in fiscal 1999, $21.5 in
fiscal 2000, and $53.1 thereafter.  These minimum lease commitments include


