NOTE L--SUBSEQUENT EVENT

On July 21, 1995, the Company acquired Sigma Imaging Systems, Inc., a privately
held company that designs and markets state-of-the-art workflow and imaging
software for paper-intensive businesses, including insurance, banking, finance,
utilities, and  government.  The Company paid approximately $20 million for
Sigma, consisting of $15 million in cash and approximately $5 million in common
stock.  Approximately $9 million in cash was paid at the end of July 1995, and
an additional $6 million will be paid during fiscal 1996.  In connection with
the acquisition, the Company anticipates a provision of approximately $20
million, that will be recorded in the first quarter of fiscal year 1996, related
to purchased research and development and the Company's overlapping development
efforts.




